MSAParser

MSHParser
The MSH Parser creates a MessageHeader Resource for MSH segments.

This class is used to give a Generic Primitive a name after it has been parsed so that it can be processed by the V2toFHIR parser.
NK1Parser
Parser for NK1 Segments The PV1 segment populates a related person resource
Normalizer
This class supports basic normalization of resources within a bundle when two or more resources of the same type may be created having the same identity.
OBRParser

OBXParser
OBXParser parses any OBX segments in a message to an Immunization if the message is a VXU or an response to an immunization query.

Parser for QAK Segments The QAK segment populates OperationOutcome.issue referenced by any generated MessageHeader.response.details with the code from QAK-2 field.
QBPUtils
This class supports construction of an HL7 QBP Message following the CDC HL7 Version 2.5.1 Implementation Guide for Immunization Messaging from HTTP GET parameters retrieved using ServletRequest.getParameters() or from a map of Strings to a list of Strings.
QIDParser
The QID Parser extracts the query tag and query name from the QID segment and attaches them to the Parameters resource.
QPDParser
The QPD Parser generates a Parameters resource documenting the QPD parameters found in QPD-3 to QPD-* For queries (message type of QBP): The Bundle.entry containing this Parameters resource in Bundle.entry.resource will contain a Bundle.entry.request element with the method set to GET and the url set to the FHIR _search URL which would perform the query.
RCPParser
The RCP Parser updates the Parameters resource generated by the QPDParser to include the count of records requested.
RXAParser
RXAParser parses any RXA segments in a message to an Immunization if the message is a VXU or an response to an immunization query.
RXRParser
RXRParser parses any RXR segments in a message to an Immunization if the message is a VXU or an response to an immunization query.
Systems
Utility class containing OIDs, URIs and names for various coding and identifier systems
TestData
TestData supports reading of HL7 messages or segments from text files in internal resources or external files, where each message or segment can have one or more assertions about the FHIR resource created from the content.
TextUtils
Utility class to convert FHIR and V2 Objects to and from strings used in text.
Units
Utility class for parsing and converting V2 ANSI, ISO+ or UCUM unit codes
V2Utils
Utilities for manipulating V2 messages for FHIR Conversion
YamlParser
YamlParser implements the HAPI FHIR IParser interface, enabling it to be used to convert FHIR Resources and elements to and from YAML
YamlUtils
This is a cleaned up implementation from the original blog post that supports converting FHIR to and from YAML format.
